'22:12': [
{sup:1, word:"Many", lines:["Verses {Psa22:12|12}-{Psa22:18|18} depict in vivid detail how Christ passed through His suffering of crucifixion (cf. {Mrk15:16|Mark 15:16}-{Mrk15:37|37}). While Christ was being crucified on the cross, many fierce men, signified by mighty bulls, encompassed Him ({Psa22:12|v. 12}). They opened their mouth at Him like a ravening and roaring lion ({Psa22:13|v. 13}). Evil men, signified by dogs (cf. {Phi3:2|Phil. 3:2a}), surrounded Him, and a congregation of evildoers enclosed Him ({Psa22:16|v. 16a-b}). They pierced His hands and feet ({Psa22:16|v. 16c}). They divided His garments to themselves, and for His clothing they cast lots ({Psa22:18|v. 18}). They also looked, stared at Him with contempt and hatred ({Psa22:17|v. 17b}). On the cross He was poured out like water ({Psa22:14|v. 14a}; {Isa53:12|Isa. 53:12}). All His bones were out of joint ({Psa22:14|v. 14b}) because He could not hold up the weight of His body as it hung on the cross. This caused Him great agony and pain. Also, He counted all His bones ({Psa22:17|v. 17a}). His heart was like wax melted within Him ({Psa22:14|v. 14c-d}). His strength was dried up like a shard ({Psa22:15|v. 15a}), a piece of broken pottery. His tongue was stuck to His jaws ({Psa22:15|v. 15b}). God had put Him in the dust of death ({Psa22:15|v. 15c})."]},
{sup:"a", word:"bulls", vrefs:"Psa. 68:30"},
],
