'22:15': [
{sup:"a", word:"dried", vrefs:"Prov. 17:22"},
{sup:1, word:"You", lines:["Referring to God. On one hand, man crucified the Lord Jesus; on the other hand, God killed Him. If Jesus had been killed only by man, He would have been merely a martyr and not our Redeemer. But God judged Him and put Him into death for our redemption ({Isa53:10|Isa. 53:10a}). All the sin of the world was laid on Christ as the Lamb of God ({Isa53:6|Isa. 53:6b}; {1Pe2:24|1&nbsp;Pet. 2:24a}; {Joh1:29|John 1:29}). On the cross He died a vicarious death for us ({2Co5:21|2&nbsp;Cor. 5:21}; {1Pe3:18|1&nbsp;Pet. 3:18}) to redeem us from our sins, from God&rsquo;s judgment, and from eternal perdition ({1Co15:3|1&nbsp;Cor. 15:3}; {Joh3:16|John 3:16}-{Joh3:17|17}; {Joh5:24|5:24})."]},
],
