'68:1': [
{sup:1, word:"Let", lines:["A quotation of Moses&rsquo; prayer in {Num10:35|Num. 10:35}, uttered when the Ark of the Covenant set out from Mount Sinai. {Psa68|Psalm 68} is the highest peak of the divine revelation concerning Christ in all the Psalms. It is written in poetry, with types and signs, portraying the steps in God&rsquo;s move on the earth in Christ. The Ark (typifying Christ&mdash;{Exo25:10|Exo. 25:10}-{Exo25:22|22} and {Exo25:10^1|notes}) was the center of the tabernacle (also typifying Christ&mdash;{Joh1:14|John 1:14}). God&rsquo;s move in the tabernacle with the Ark among Israel, His elect, from Sinai to Zion typifies the Triune God&rsquo;s move in Christ as His all-inclusive embodiment from Christ&rsquo;s incarnation to His ascension. In the type, God&rsquo;s move was from Sinai (vv. {Psa68:8|8b}, {Psa68:17|17b}), beginning with the decreeing of the law and the erecting of the tabernacle, which signifies the incarnated Christ, through the wilderness (vv. {Psa68:4|4b}, {Psa68:7|7b}), which signifies the earth, to Mount Zion ({Psa68:16|v. 16}), God&rsquo;s dwelling place, which signifies God&rsquo;s dwelling place in the heavens ({Rev14:1|Rev. 14:1}). In the reality, God&rsquo;s move in Christ and through Christ for the accomplishing of His New Testament economy began with Christ&rsquo;s incarnation, which was the setting up of the real and living tabernacle in whom God dwelt and through whom He could move on earth; continued through Christ&rsquo;s human living on the earth with His crucifixion and resurrection; and concluded with Christ&rsquo;s ascension to Zion in the heavens. This unique move of God is portrayed in vv. {Psa68:1|1}-{Psa68:18|18} of this psalm. See {Eph4:8^1|note 8<sup>1</sup>} in {Eph4|Eph. 4}."]},
{sup:"a", word:"arise", vrefs:"Num. 10:35; Isa. 33:3"},
{sup:2, word:"enemies", lines:["The enemies here typify Satan and his forces of evil in the heavenlies ({Eph6:12|Eph. 6:12}). This prayer is actually the aspiration of all God&rsquo;s elect. Cf. {Psa68:12^1|note 12<sup>1</sup>}."]},
],
'68:2': [
{sup:"a", word:"before", vrefs:"Rev. 6:16"},
],
'68:4': [
{sup:1, word:"Triumph", lines:["Indicating that Israel, God&rsquo;s elect, triumphed in God and exulted before Him in His move on the earth. Today we too should exult in the move of God on earth from Christ&rsquo;s incarnation to His ascension."]},
{sup:"a", word:"deserts", vrefs:"Jer. 2:6"},
{sup:"2b", word:"Jah", vrefs:"Isa. 12:2; 26:4; 38:11", lines:["A shortened form of Jehovah."]},
],
'68:5': [
{sup:1, word:"orphans", lines:["God causes the believers in Christ as the needy ones (the orphans and widows), the bound ones (the prisoners&mdash;{Psa68:6|v. 6}), and the solitary ones ({Psa68:6|v. 6}) to dwell in His habitation, the church ({1Ti3:15|1&nbsp;Tim. 3:15}). The church is a building that includes such people."]},
{sup:"a", word:"habitation", vrefs:"Deut. 12:5; Psa. 26:8; 132:13"},
],
