'69:1': [
{sup:1, word:"Save", lines:["{Psa69|Psalm 69} is on the suffering Christ, typified by the suffering David, and {Psa72|Psa. 72} is on the reigning Christ, typified by the reigning Solomon. In this psalm the sufferings of Christ are portrayed in a detailed way: Christ was hated by many without cause ({Psa69:4|v. 4a}; {Joh15:25|John 15:25}); He was reproached for the sake of God (vv. {Psa69:7|7a}, {Psa69:9|9b}; {Rom15:3|Rom. 15:3}); He was devoured by the zeal of God&rsquo;s house ({Psa69:9|v. 9a}; {Joh2:17|John 2:17}); He suffered much, and no one took pity on Him (vv. {Psa69:29|29a}, {Psa69:19|19}-{Psa69:20|20}; {Joh16:32|John 16:32}); He wept and entreated God to deliver Him out of death (vv. {Psa69:10|10}, {Psa69:13|13}-{Psa69:17|17}, {Psa69:1|1}-{Psa69:2|2}; {Heb5:7|Heb. 5:7}); He was given gall as His food while He was suffering on the cross ({Psa69:21|v. 21a}; {Mat27:34|Matt. 27:34}); He was given vinegar to drink in His thirst on the cross ({Psa69:21|v. 21b}; {Joh19:28|John 19:28}-{Joh19:30|30}); He was stricken and wounded by God ({Psa69:26|v. 26}; {Isa53:10|Isa. 53:10a}); and He was betrayed by one of His disciples ({Psa69:25|v. 25}; {Act1:16|Acts 1:16}-{Act1:20|20a}). After His life of suffering on earth, typified by the sufferings of David, Christ ascended to the heavens, where He is now reigning as the King, typified by Solomon."]},
],
