'89:1': [
{sup:1, word:"I", lines:["{Psa89|Psalm 89}, especially vv. {Psa89:3|3}-{Psa89:4|4}, {Psa89:19|19}-{Psa89:29|29}, and {Psa89:34|34}-{Psa89:37|37}, unveils the intention of God that Christ, His Anointed, would possess the entire earth. In vv. {Psa89:19|19}-{Psa89:20|20} Christ, the unique One in God&rsquo;s record ({Psa87:6|87:6}), has become God&rsquo;s Holy One, God&rsquo;s mighty One, God&rsquo;s anointed One ({Act2:27|Acts 2:27}; {Isa9:6|Isa. 9:6}; {Mat1:16|Matt. 1:16}). He calls God His Father and His God ({Psa89:26|v. 26}; {Joh20:17|John 20:17}). He has become the Firstborn and &ldquo;the highest of the kings of the earth&rdquo; ({Psa89:27|v. 27}; {Rom8:29|Rom. 8:29}; {Rev1:5|Rev. 1:5a}). His throne will be like the sun before God; it will be established forever like the moon (vv. {Psa89:36|36}-{Psa89:37|37}; {Psa72:5|72:5}). God will establish His seed forever and &ldquo;His throne as the days of heaven&rdquo; ({Psa89:29|v. 29}). God will extend the territory of this unique One so that He will possess the entire earth, setting &ldquo;His hand on the sea and His right hand on the rivers&rdquo; ({Psa89:25|v. 25}; cf. {Rev10:1|Rev. 10:1}-{Rev10:2|2}). The sea probably refers to the Mediterranean Sea, the center of the populated earth. That Christ&rsquo;s territory will be extended to all the rivers indicates that Christ will possess all the parts of the earth, signified by their rivers; that is, He will possess the whole earth ({Psa2:8|2:8}). Both Book Two and Book Three end with the extension of God&rsquo;s kingdom to the whole earth ({Psa72:8|72:8}, {Psa72:11|11}, {Psa72:19|19}; {Psa89:25|89:25}, {Psa89:27|27})."]},
],
