'109:1': [
{sup:1, word:"O", lines:["{Psa109|Psalm 109} is a prayer of David concerning his sufferings and is also a description of his sufferings. David here is a type of Christ, and David&rsquo;s sufferings typify Christ&rsquo;s sufferings in His flesh ({Heb5:7|Heb. 5:7}-{Heb5:8|8}; {1Pe4:1|1&nbsp;Pet. 4:1}). This is indicated by the fact that {Psa109:8|v. 8} is quoted in {Act1:20|Acts 1:20} and applied to Judas, who betrayed Christ.","David&rsquo;s prayer in this psalm typifies Christ&rsquo;s prayer ({Heb5:7|Heb. 5:7} and {Heb5:7^1|note}). The prayer in this psalm is answered in the next, which unveils Christ in His ascension, indicating that God&rsquo;s answer to Christ&rsquo;s prayer was not only through resurrection but also in ascension."]},
],
