'119:15': [
{sup:1, word:"muse", lines:["Rich in meaning, the Hebrew word for muse (often translated meditate in the KJV) implies to worship, to converse with oneself, and to speak aloud. To muse on the word is to taste and enjoy it through careful considering. Prayer, speaking to oneself, and praising the Lord may also be included in musing on the word. To muse on the word of God is to enjoy His word as His breath ({2Ti3:16|2&nbsp;Tim. 3:16}) and thus to be infused with God, to breathe God in, and to receive spiritual nourishment."]},
],
