'119:50': [
{sup:"1a", word:"enlivened", vrefs:"Psa. 119:25", lines:["There are two aspects of the law&mdash;the aspect of the letter and the aspect of the Spirit. &ldquo;The letter kills, but the Spirit gives life&rdquo; ({2Co3:6|2&nbsp;Cor. 3:6}). If our attitude in coming to the law is to care only for the commandments in letters, we will have the law in the aspect of the killing letter. However, if we take every part of the law&mdash;all the commandments, ordinances, statutes, precepts, and judgments&mdash;as the word breathed out by the God whom we love, we will have the law in the aspect of the life-giving Spirit.","The function of the law also has two aspects. On the negative side, the law exposes man&rsquo;s sin ({Rom3:20|Rom. 3:20b}; {Rom7:7|7:7b}) and subdues sinners before God ({Rom3:19|Rom. 3:19}). It also guards God&rsquo;s chosen people in its custody that they might be conducted to Christ ({Gal3:23|Gal. 3:23}-{Gal3:24|24}). On the positive side, as God&rsquo;s living testimony, the law functions to minister the living God to His seekers (vv. {Psa119:2|2}, {Psa119:88|88}), and as God&rsquo;s living word, the law functions to dispense God Himself as life and light into those who love the law (vv. {Psa119:25|25}, {Psa119:116|116}, {Psa119:130|130}). See {Exo19:8^1P3|note 8<sup>1</sup>, par. 3}, in {Exo19|Exo. 19}."]},
],
